initial_story:
The Eurovision Song Contest is just around the corner and this year, it's taking place in Malmo, Sweden.

You can find out all about the event right here.

The UK's entry for 2024 is Olly Alexander who'll be performing his song, Dizzy.

But how's he feeling ahead of the big night, where he'll perform in front of 200 million people!

De-Graft sat down with him to find out all about his preparation for the competition.

The Eurovision Song contest Grand Final will be shown on BBC One and iPlayer on Saturday 11 May.
stories: Olly, you're just weeks away from taking the stage at Eurovision, how's your preparation going? "I'm feeling really good, to be honest," he says with a smile. "I've been working so hard on the performance, making sure everything is perfect. The song, Dizzy, is a real showstopper and I'm so excited to share it with the world."

"I've also been doing a lot of vocal exercises to make sure my voice is in top condition for the big night. And, of course, I've been rehearsing with the backing dancers to make sure we're all on the same page. I have to say, the whole team is just incredible, we all gel so well together. I'm really proud of what we've put together."

"I've been thinking a lot about the set list too, and I've decided to add a few surprises to keep the crowd engaged. I want to make sure everyone leaves the venue feeling like they've had an unforgettable experience. The costume designer has been working overtime to create some amazing outfits, and I think the lighting and special effects are going to be just incredible. I'm feeling really good about how everything is coming together, and I just can't wait to get out there and perform."

"I've also been thinking about the opener, and I'm really excited to announce that we're going to have a special guest joining us on stage. I think their unique sound and energy will really get the crowd pumped up and set the tone for the rest of the show. Plus, I've been chatting with the promoter and they're predicting a sell-out crowd, which is just amazing. I'm truly grateful for all the support we've been getting leading up to this tour. It's going to be a night to remember!"

"I've been working with the special guest to tailor a special setlist that will blend our own music with some of their biggest hits, and trust me, it's going to be a real game-changer. We're also planning some surprise giveaways and prizes for the best fans in the crowd, so be sure to get there early and show your enthusiasm. And to top it all off, we've arranged for a meet-and-greet with the special guest after the show, so don't miss your chance to get up close and personal with your new favorite artist!"

"The special guest has given us an exclusive preview of their new single, and we can't wait to share it with you for the very first time live on stage. We're also partnering with a local charity to make this show an unforgettable experience, with a portion of the proceeds going towards a great cause. Don't forget to bring your phone and be ready to capture the memories, as we'll have a special social media contest with prizes for the best posts and photos. See you all there!"

"The doors will open at 7pm, and the show will kick off at 8pm sharp, so make sure to arrive early to grab a good spot. We'll also have a limited edition merchandise booth available, featuring exclusive items only available at this event. And as a special treat, the special guest will be doing an exclusive meet-and-greet with a select few lucky winners, so be sure to follow our social media accounts for details on how to enter to win!"

"In addition, we'll have a pre-show playlist spinning your favorite tunes starting at 6:30pm to get you in the mood, and our concessions stand will be serving up a variety of delicious treats to keep you fueled throughout the night. Don't miss out on the fun - mark your calendars for an unforgettable evening with [artist/band name]!"

"...as the walls of the mansion seem to shift and writhe like living things, and the air is thick with the scent of decay and forgotten memories.
